    public class KeyStructureWritable
extends java.lang.Object
implements org.apache.hadoop.io.WritableComparable<KeyStructureWritable>
    The key structure used by mapper and reducers. It is of paramount importance that the Key element do not know an image, since it is desirable for it to be as small as possible.

    Marco Aurelio Lotz

      • hashCode

        public int hashCode()
        The default partitioner is the HashPartitioner, which uses the hashCode method to determine which reducer to send the K,V pair to. For this reason, objects with the same key should give the same hash value. In this implementation the hashCode is given by the SeriesInstanceUID Hash.
